    <svcproc id="s26510.2.13" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAP Sensor (Manifold Absolute Pressure)</title>
        <figure id="e3001113" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>MAP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>A ceramic diaphragm sensor installed in the right front top of the intake manifold next to the inlet air
            elbow. The ECM monitors the MAP signal to determine intake manifold pressure (boost). This information is
            used to control the Boost Control Solenoid (BCS).
        </para>
